\section{Return-type note}{

\code{get_statistical_security} and \code{get_num_adversarial_queries}
return \code{double} rather than \code{integer}. This matches an
inconsistency in the upstream Params base class: the
corresponding setters take \code{uint32_t} but the getters return
\code{double}. The underlying field is a \code{double} — R binds per the
header, not per the setter signature.

\code{get_plaintext_modulus} returns an R \code{integer} on 32-bit-safe
values; for moduli that exceed the 32-bit signed integer range
the return value is a \code{numeric} (double) carrying a losslessly
rounded 53-bit integer, per the \code{design.md} §7 return-type
convention.
}

